---
import '../styles/global.css';
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout lang="en" title="Privacy Policy - OmixAI" description="OmixAI privacy policy. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when using our proteomics analysis services." lightHeader={false}>
	<section class="bg-section-alt py-16">
		<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
			<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl text-heading animate-fade-in-up">
				Privacy Policy
			</h1>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="py-12 bg-section">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none text-body space-y-8">

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">1. General Provisions</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						OmixAI Inc. (hereinafter "Company") places great importance on protecting the personal information of users. We are committed to ensuring that personal information provided to the Company online while using our services is protected. The Company complies with personal information protection regulations under relevant laws and guidelines.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
						Through this Privacy Policy, we inform users about how their personal information is used, for what purposes, and what measures are taken to protect it. This Privacy Policy may be amended from time to time due to changes in government laws and guidelines or internal company policies, and any changes will be notified through our website.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">2. Consent to Collection of Personal Information</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						The Company has established procedures for users to click "I Agree" or "I Do Not Agree" buttons regarding the Privacy Policy or Terms of Use. Clicking "I Agree" is considered consent to the collection of personal information.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">3. Purpose of Collection and Use of Personal Information</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						"Personal information" refers to information about a living individual that can identify the individual through name, email, contact information, etc. The Company collects and uses personal information for the following purposes:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted mt-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Name, email, contact, organization: Processing service inquiries and responses</li>
						<li>Email, organization: Sample report downloads</li>
						<li>Providing proteomics analysis services and contract fulfillment</li>
						<li>Business partnership and collaboration inquiries</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">4. Items of Personal Information Collected and Collection Methods</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						The Company collects essential information for service provision through website contact forms.
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted mt-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Contact form: Name, email, organization, inquiry details</li>
						<li>Sample report download: Email, organization</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
						We do not collect sensitive personal information that may infringe on users' fundamental rights, and we do not use the information provided for purposes other than those stated in advance.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">5. Automatic Collection of Personal Information</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						The Company may use cookies to provide customized services to users. Cookies are small pieces of information that a website sends to your computer browser. Users can refuse cookie installation through browser settings, but this may cause difficulties in using some services.
					</p>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
						<strong>Cookie Settings:</strong>
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted mt-2 space-y-1">
						<li>Chrome: Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and other site data</li>
						<li>Safari: Preferences → Privacy</li>
						<li>Edge: Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">6. Sharing and Provision of Personal Information</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						The Company uses users' personal information only within the scope stated in the purpose of collection and use, and does not use it beyond that scope or disclose it to external parties without prior consent. However, the following cases are exceptions:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted mt-4 space-y-2">
						<li>When users have given prior consent to disclosure</li>
						<li>When necessary to fulfill a service contract</li>
						<li>When required by law or when requested by investigative agencies according to legal procedures</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">7. Access, Correction, and Deletion of Personal Information</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						Users may request to view, correct, or delete their personal information held by the Company at any time. For personal information-related requests, please contact the Privacy Officer listed below for prompt processing.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">8. Retention and Use Period of Personal Information</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						In principle, users' personal information is destroyed when the purpose of collection or provision is achieved. However, if preservation is required under relevant laws, the Company retains member information for the period specified by relevant laws.
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside text-muted mt-4 space-y-2">
						<li>Records on contracts or withdrawal of subscription: 5 years</li>
						<li>Records on payment and supply of goods: 5 years</li>
						<li>Records on consumer complaints or dispute resolution: 3 years</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-4">
						When destroying personal information, printed personal information is shredded or incinerated, and electronically stored personal information is deleted using technical methods that make the records irreproducible.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">9. Users' Rights and Obligations</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						Users are advised to enter accurate and up-to-date personal information to prevent accidents. Users are responsible for accidents caused by inaccurate information they have entered. Users have the right to have their personal information protected and also have the obligation to protect themselves and not infringe on others' information.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">10. Privacy Officer</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						The Company has designated a Privacy Officer responsible for handling opinions and complaints regarding personal information.
					</p>
					<div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-[var(--bg-input)] rounded-lg">
						<p class="text-body"><strong>Privacy Officer:</strong> Dongmyung Shin, Ph.D.</p>
						<p class="text-muted">Email: <a href="mailto:omixai@omixai.com" class="text-[var(--brand-teal)] hover:underline">omixai@omixai.com</a></p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">11. Protection of Children's Personal Information</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						The Company does not collect personal information from children under the age of 14 to protect their personal information.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="glass-card rounded-xl p-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl text-heading mb-4">12. Obligation of Notification</h2>
					<p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
						Any additions, deletions, or modifications to this Privacy Policy due to changes in government policies or security technologies will be notified through our website.
					</p>
					<div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-[var(--bg-input)] rounded-lg">
						<p class="text-muted">Privacy Policy Effective Date: January 10, 2025</p>
					</div>
				</div>

			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
